Pir-e-Kamil (or Peer-e-Kamil), (Urdu: پیر کامل صلی اللہ علیہ و آلہ و سلم‎) meaning The Perfect Mentor, is a fiction novel authored by Pakistani writer Umera Ahmad. It was first published in Urdu in 2004 and later in English in 2011. The book deals with the turning points in intervening lives of two people: a runaway girl named Imama Hashim; and a boy named Salar Sikander having an IQ level above 150. The story spans a time period of around ten years.It is Ahmad's most popular work.